14. Sample Code
---------------

#include <iostream>
#include <stack>
using namespace std;

int main() {

    stack<int> st;

    st.push(10);
    st.push(20);
    st.push(30);

    cout << "Top: " << st.top() << endl;

    st.pop();

    cout << "Top after pop: " << st.top() << endl;

    cout << "Size: " << st.size() << endl;

    cout << "Empty: " << (st.empty() ? "Yes" : "No") << endl;

    return 0;
}

-----------------------------------------

15. Limitations
---------------
❌ No indexing (st[i])
❌ No iteration
❌ No random access

-----------------------------------------

16. KEY INTERVIEW SUMMARY
-------------------------
- Stack = LIFO container adaptor
- Default container = deque
- Only top accessible
- No iteration allowed
- push/pop/top are O(1)

